    • Method Detail

      • createMessage

        public static String createMessage(String message,
                   String[] value)
        Strings of messages can be defined with format elements (e.g. compare to printf("%d", x) in C program language). The format element used here is "%v". Every message can have a number of format elements. The appropriate values are stored in an array of strings.

        Format elements in the message are replaced by array elements regarding the number of format elements and the number of array elements.
        Parameters:
        message - The message with or without format elements.
        value - Array of strings with values which replaces the format elements.
        Returns:
        Message string with replaced format elements.
